他来找你了 杰克 来报仇了
He's coming for you Jack, to seek revenge.

360
00:36:42,290 --> 00:36:43,830
死人的传说就是这样讲的
As the dead man's tale is told...

361
00:36:44,040 --> 00:36:45,500
我不相信你
I don't believe you.

362
00:36:48,210 --> 00:36:49,260
他怎么说
What did he say?

363
00:36:49,340 --> 00:36:50,880
他说你的罗盘是
He said your compass was the key

364
00:36:50,960 --> 00:36:52,890
他逃脱的关键 一支死人的大军
to his escape. An army of dead,

365
00:36:52,970 --> 00:36:54,590
直接朝着你来了 杰克
are coming straight for you, Jack.

366
00:36:54,800 --> 00:36:57,260
海神三叉戟是你的唯一的希望
The Trident of Poseidon is your only hope.

367
00:36:59,310 --> 00:37:00,770
我们说定了吗
Do we have an accord?

368
00:37:09,400 --> 00:37:12,740
- 我才不要去那里告诉他 - 是你的主意
- I am not going in there to tell him. - It was your idea!

369
00:37:12,820 --> 00:37:15,830
不 我的主意是让你去告诉他
No, it was my idea for you to tell him.

370
00:37:15,910 --> 00:37:17,580
他更喜欢你
He likes you more than me.

371
00:37:17,660 --> 00:37:19,410
他不喜欢任何人
He doesn't like anybody.

372
00:37:42,310 --> 00:37:45,230
抱歉 先生 我们知道您说过永远不要打扰您
Sorry sir. We know you said never to disturb you.

373
00:37:45,310 --> 00:37:47,230
或者没有好的理由就跑过来
Or to come in without good cause.

374
00:37:47,310 --> 00:37:49,150
或者开口说话前没有先
Or to speak without first.

375
00:37:50,480 --> 00:37:52,400
请教您我们的想法
To ask you now whether our,

376
00:37:52,480 --> 00:37:54,990
是不是绝对必要
thoughts were absolutely necessary.

377
00:37:55,150 --> 00:37:57,200
好比那一次我们的船着火了
Like the time the ship was on fire.

378
00:37:57,280 --> 00:37:59,290
那是一个必要的想法的例子
That being an example of necessary thought.

379
00:37:59,370 --> 00:38:02,580
所以 我们再次为引发那场火道歉
So again, we do apologize for starting that fire.

380
00:38:09,460 --> 00:38:10,500
讲
Speak!

381
00:38:10,960 --> 00:38:14,590
是我们的船 先生 它们正在遭受敌人的攻击
It's the ships, sir. They are being attacked by an enemy...

382
00:38:14,670 --> 00:38:18,260
- 敌人抢走了财宝 - 他们随随便便就会杀人
- That takes the Riches. - Kills without provocation.

383
00:38:18,340 --> 00:38:21,140
我的船 不可能
My ships? Not possible!

384
00:38:21,220 --> 00:38:23,350
其中的三艘已经沉了 先生
Three of them already been sunk, Sir.

385
00:38:23,560 --> 00:38:26,270
下手的是一个叫萨拉曼达的船长
They have been sunk by a captain called Salamander!

386
00:38:26,430 --> 00:38:27,810
萨拉查
Salazar.

387
00:38:29,400 --> 00:38:30,560
萨拉查
Salazar!

388
00:38:30,770 --> 00:38:34,280
就是他 先生大人 他在每一艘船上留下一个活口
That's him, your sireness! He leaves one man from each vessel...

389
00:38:34,360 --> 00:38:38,610
来讲他的故事 整个舰队都在沉没
To tell the tale. The entire fleet is being sunk.

390
00:38:38,990 --> 00:38:41,660
我们马上就要死了
And we'll soon be dead.

391
00:38:42,490 --> 00:38:45,040
而且很有可能关门大吉
And quite possibly out of business.

392
00:38:51,290 --> 00:38:53,710
我需要和你们的女巫待一段时间
I'll be needing some time with your witch...

393
00:39:08,730 --> 00:39:13,730
我一直在等你 船长 你要喝杯茶吗
I have been expecting you Captain. Perhaps you would like some tea.

394
00:39:17,400 --> 00:39:19,740
不用了 非常感谢
I shall pass, thank you kindly.

395
00:39:21,070 --> 00:39:24,410
进我的门的代价是鲜血 船长
The price of crossing my door is blood, Captain.

396
00:39:25,330 --> 00:39:28,000
这就解释了为什么你生意这么冷清
That explains why you're not so busy.

397
00:39:28,710 --> 00:39:31,000
每个人最终都会付出代价的
Everyone pays, eventually.

398
00:39:32,420 --> 00:39:35,090
沙萨 你我很久以前就有交情了
Shansa, you and I made a bond long ago.

399
00:39:35,380 --> 00:39:36,880
我把你从绞刑架上救了下来
I saved you from the gallows.

400
00:39:37,050 --> 00:39:37,800
记得吗
Remember?

401
00:39:37,880 --> 00:39:40,220
而我也诅咒了你的敌人
And I cursed your enemies.

402
00:39:40,340 --> 00:39:42,810
现在你心怀恐惧来找我
But now you come to me with fear.

403
00:39:42,890 --> 00:39:46,100
在死人统治了大海的时候
As the dead have taken command over the sea.

404
00:39:46,180 --> 00:39:49,400
死人找我做什么
And what would the dead be wanting with me?

405
00:39:49,480 --> 00:39:51,600
不是你 船长
Not you, Captain.

406
00:39:51,900 --> 00:39:55,650
- 他们在找斯派洛 - 杰克？
- They're searching for a Sparrow. - Jack?

407
00:39:58,570 --> 00:40:04,700
杰克会乘船去找三叉戟 带着一个女孩和一颗珍珠
Jack who sails for the trident... With a girl and a Pearl.

408
00:40:05,410 --> 00:40:08,370
三叉戟永远不能被找到
The trident can never be found.

409
00:40:11,710 --> 00:40:14,500
三叉戟是杰克唯一的希望
The trident is Jack's only hope.

410
00:40:14,630 --> 00:40:16,420
死者统治了大海
The dead are conquering the sea,

411
00:40:16,500 --> 00:40:18,920
却无法登上陆地
unable to step on dry land.

412
00:40:21,840 --> 00:40:24,840
也许你该退休 回到乡下生活了
Maybe you should retire to the country side.

413
00:40:27,140 --> 00:40:28,810
你说回到草地吗
You mean grass?

414
00:40:29,680 --> 00:40:31,020
在农场里
On a farm?

415
00:40:31,770 --> 00:40:34,350
给牛挤奶 制作奶酪
Milking a cow, making cheese.

416
00:40:34,980 --> 00:40:40,150
- 看着他们把我的财宝都沉掉 - 船长 请你自己想想
- While they sink mi treasure? - Ask yourself this, Captain.

417
00:40:40,740 --> 00:40:44,910
- 这些财宝值得你去死吗 - 我是一个海盗
- Is this treasure worth dying for? - I'm a pirate.

418
00:40:45,620 --> 00:40:48,830
永远都是 所以我该怎么保护
Always will be! So how do I save,

419
00:40:48,910 --> 00:40:51,630
- 属于我的东西 - 杰克有一个罗盘
- what be mine. - Jack held a compass.

420
00:40:51,710 --> 00:40:54,460
会指给你你最渴望的东西
Which points you to the thing you desire most.

421
00:40:54,540 --> 00:40:56,630
但是你如果背叛罗盘
But betray the compass...

422
00:40:56,880 --> 00:40:59,260
它就会释放你最大的恐惧
And it releases your greatest fear.

423
00:40:59,340 --> 00:41:02,920
而一个海盗最大的恐惧是萨拉查 是吧
And a pirate's greatest fear will be Salazar, is it?

424
00:41:06,470 --> 00:41:09,600
- 你怎么拿到这个的 - 我自有办法
- How did you get this? - I have my ways.

425
00:41:09,810 --> 00:41:12,770
把他们带向杰克 在他找到三叉戟之前
Lead them to Jack before he finds the trident.

426
00:41:13,020 --> 00:41:16,650
这样你的财宝都会回到你的手中
And all your treasure will come back to you.

427
00:41:18,150 --> 00:41:20,690
是时候和死者做一笔交易了
Time to make a deal with the dead.

428
00:41:23,950 --> 00:41:25,700
快点 海盗
Come on, pirate.

429
00:41:32,700 --> 00:41:34,080
等一下 停
Hold on, stop.

430
00:41:39,290 --> 00:41:43,130
- 杰克叔叔 - 小杰 你怎么样
- Uncle Jack! - Jackie boy, how is it going?

431
00:41:43,210 --> 00:41:44,970
没什么可抱怨的 你呢
Can't complain really. You?

432
00:41:45,050 --> 00:41:47,430
我在这里等了一上午了 等着被打一顿
I've been waiting all morning in here, for a beating.

433
00:41:47,550 --> 00:41:50,430
- 但是这里的服务太差了 - 太不像话了
- But the service is terrible. - Shameful.

434
00:41:50,930 --> 00:41:51,970
杰克
Jack.

435
00:41:53,850 --> 00:41:56,110
海洋将被鲜血染红
The oceans have turned to blood.

436
00:41:56,190 --> 00:41:59,110
你最好待在陆地上 那里比较安全
Best to stay on dry land, where it's safe.

437
00:41:59,690 --> 00:42:02,780
我就要在陆地上被处死了
I'm about to be executed on dry land.

438
00:42:02,860 --> 00:42:03,780
有道理
Good point.

439
00:42:03,860 --> 00:42:06,030
我给你讲过骷髅的故事吗
Did I ever told you about the skeleton?

440
00:42:06,150 --> 00:42:07,410
你讲过 讲过好多次了
Yes you have, many times.

441
00:42:07,490 --> 00:42:10,200
骷髅走进一个酒馆 点了一杯酒
Skeleton goes into a bar, orders a beer.

442
00:42:10,370 --> 00:42:11,620
还要了一个拖把
And a mop.

443
00:42:13,790 --> 00:42:15,000
一如既往地好笑
Funny as ever.

444
00:42:15,500 --> 00:42:16,620
好了 走吧
Come on let's go!

445
00:42:17,790 --> 00:42:23,050
如果他们要开你的膛 记得找维克托 他手法最好
If they disembowel you, ask for Viktor. He's got the softest hands.

446
00:42:23,420 --> 00:42:24,050
谢了！
Thank you!

447
00:42:24,130 --> 00:42:26,930
提我的名字 他们就不会砍掉你的脚
And mention my name, they won't cut your feet off.

448
00:42:47,360 --> 00:42:49,820
来吧 你是第一个
Come on. You're first!

449
00:42:52,780 --> 00:42:55,080
海盗 你想怎么死
And how would you like to die pirate?

450
00:42:55,160 --> 00:42:59,080
绞死 枪决 还有一个新的发明
Hanging, firing squad or a new invention.

451
00:42:59,170 --> 00:43:01,420
- 断头台 - 断头台
- The guillotine. - Guillotine?

452
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:03,970
听起来像法国的东西 我喜欢法国的东西
Sounds french. I love the French.

453
00:43:04,050 --> 00:43:06,050
你知道他们发明了蛋黄酱吗
Did you know they've invented mayonnaise?

454
00:43:06,170 --> 00:43:08,430
能有多差劲 是法国的 对吧
How bad could it be? It's French, right?

455
00:43:12,180 --> 00:43:14,640
哦 我的锅 我改变主意啦
Oh, my bad! I change mi mind...

456
00:43:20,770 --> 00:43:23,980
请可怜可怜我 我睡觉都尿床的
No please have mercy for me. I am a bed wetter.

457
00:43:41,170 --> 00:43:42,340
不是吧
Oh, come on!

458
00:43:42,420 --> 00:43:44,970
我为这事还要爬楼梯吗
I mean I have to walk upstairs as well for this?

459
00:43:45,050 --> 00:43:48,590
- 把篮子拿过来 - 篮子 干什么用的
- Bring the basket. - Basket... why?

460
00:43:50,300 --> 00:43:51,380
把他摁倒
Step him down!

461
00:43:59,310 --> 00:44:01,690
我有个主意
Here's an idea.

462
00:44:01,810 --> 00:44:05,980
要不我们试试传统的石刑吧 我现在很希望被石刑处死
Why don't we try good old fashioned stoning? I'd kill to be stoned right now.

463
00:44:06,230 --> 00:44:08,030
能让人群都参与进来 不是吗
Gets the crowd involved, doesn't it?

464
00:44:08,320 --> 00:44:10,240
我希望就开膛一事同维克托谈谈
I should like to speak to Victor in disembowelment.

465
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:11,530
我希望同维克谈谈
I should like to speak to Vic.

466
00:44:13,200 --> 00:44:15,200
我一般很少抱怨
I'm not the one who, complain normally,

467
00:44:15,370 --> 00:44:17,410
但是这个篮子里都是脑袋
but this basket is full of heads.

468
00:44:26,800 --> 00:44:30,380
卡丽娜·史密斯的遗言 安静
Final words of Carina Smyth. quiet!

469
00:44:35,050 --> 00:44:37,010
卡丽娜·史密斯的遗言
The final words of Carina Smyth.

470
00:44:37,470 --> 00:44:39,770
她说 我不是个女巫
It says. I'm not a witch.

471
00:44:39,850 --> 00:44:43,230
但是我原谅了你们这常见的愚蠢的无知和低能的大脑
But I forgive your common dim witlessness and feeble brains.

472
00:44:43,400 --> 00:44:45,440
简单来说 你们大部分人都有个羊脑子
In short, most of you have the mind of a goat.

473
00:44:45,520 --> 00:44:47,610
请原谅 长官 对于那些将要被处死之人
Pardon me sir. It's not common practice...

474
00:44:47,690 --> 00:44:49,450
这不是常见的做法吧
for those about to be executed.

475
00:44:49,530 --> 00:44:52,120
让他们留下遗言 或者说 类似的
To be granted a last, I don't know, some of a...?

476
00:44:52,200 --> 00:44:54,950
我正在说话 麻烦你耐心一点
I believe I was making a point. If you could just be patient.

477
00:44:55,240 --> 00:44:56,370
不
No.

478
00:44:56,530 --> 00:44:59,410
我脑袋就要被砍掉了 我这里很急
My head's about to be lopped off. Hence the urgency.

479
00:44:59,490 --> 00:45:00,920
我脖子还要断掉了呢
And my neck is to be broken.

480
00:45:01,000 --> 00:45:03,670
你是否知道在个别情况下 脖子并不真的会断掉
Did you know that on occasion, the neck doesn't actually break.

481
00:45:03,750 --> 00:45:05,630
- 只是会很疼 - 什么
- It just hurts. - What?

482
00:45:05,710 --> 00:45:06,710
是的
Oh Yes.

483
00:45:07,000 --> 00:45:08,550
我见过有的人挂了好几个小时
I have seen men swing for hours.

484
00:45:08,630 --> 00:45:10,130
眼珠凸出 舌头膨胀
Eyes bulging, tongues swelling.

485
00:45:10,210 --> 00:45:12,220
- 发出恶心的咯咯声 - 能让我说完吗
- Revolting gurgling sound. - May I finish?

486
00:45:12,300 --> 00:45:13,840
不能 你太幸运了
No. You're lucky.

487
00:45:14,050 --> 00:45:15,390
我还想被绞死呢
Wish I was hung.

488
00:45:16,300 --> 00:45:18,850
- 先杀了这个破海盗 我等着 - 女巫优先！
- Kill the filthy pirate, I'll wait... - The witch is first!

489
00:45:18,930 --> 00:45:20,850
我不是女巫 你有没有在听啊
I'm not a witch. Did not you listen?

490
00:45:20,930 --> 00:45:23,020
有个羊脑子很难认真听的
Quite hard to listen when you have the mind of a goat.

491
00:45:23,100 --> 00:45:24,810
够了 两个人都杀了
Enough! Kill them both.

492
00:45:24,890 --> 00:45:26,310
好
Yes!

493
00:45:46,670 --> 00:45:50,500
想多了吧 你以为你能打败我们
Guess another news. Did you think you could defeat us boy?

494
00:45:50,670 --> 00:45:53,090
不 先生 我只是转移注意力的
No sir, I'm just a diversion.

495
00:45:53,920 --> 00:45:55,510
开火
Fire!

496
00:46:21,370 --> 00:46:23,080
我还是想被石刑
I still rather be stoned.

497
00:46:28,250 --> 00:46:29,710
装弹
Reload!

498
00:46:49,600 --> 00:46:50,650
谢了
Thank you.

499
00:47:00,570 --> 00:47:02,950
过来 你个海盗渣滓
Come here. You Pirate Scum!

500
00:47:03,030 --> 00:47:04,040
嘿
Hey!

501
00:47:13,040 --> 00:47:15,130
你干什么 不不不不
What do you do? No, no, no, no!

502
00:47:25,720 --> 00:47:26,890
马
Horses?

503
00:47:45,330 --> 00:47:47,580
- 谢谢你 - 不客气 小姐
- Thank you. - You're welcome Mi lady.

504
00:47:49,410 --> 00:47:50,460
接住你了
Got you!

505
00:47:56,380 --> 00:47:58,090
你来接谁来了 叛徒
Who you'd come tolling back traitor?

506
00:47:58,170 --> 00:47:59,470
那个叫特纳的小伙子给了我们
The Turner boy gave us...

507
00:47:59,550 --> 00:48:01,930
十个银币来救你
Ten pieces of silver to save your neck.

508
00:48:08,930 --> 00:48:10,650
从这一刻起我们是盟友了
From this moment on we're to be allies.

509
00:48:10,730 --> 00:48:12,150
考虑到你左手的位置
Considering where your left hand is.

510
00:48:12,230 --> 00:48:14,400
- 我看我们可不只是盟友 - 我们一起去找三叉戟
- I'd say we're more than that. - We'd find the Trident together.

511
00:48:14,480 --> 00:48:15,280
你能向我承诺吗
Do I have your word?

512
00:48:15,360 --> 00:48:17,190
除了承诺我什么都要给你了
You're holding everything but my word.

513
00:48:17,440 --> 00:48:19,740
那我把拯救我的荣誉赠予你
Then I bestow upon you the honor of saving me.

514
00:48:19,820 --> 00:48:20,950
只收一点点赞助费
For a small donation.

515
00:48:21,110 --> 00:48:23,490
你指望我们付钱给你来救你
You expect us to pay you to save you?

516
00:48:24,950 --> 00:48:25,950
是的
Yes!

517
00:48:27,700 --> 00:48:29,290
就收十个银币
For a mere 10 pieces.

518
00:48:35,540 --> 00:48:36,710
疯了
Madness!

519
00:48:37,050 --> 00:48:39,420
- 我们不会付超过五个 - 那行吧
- We won't pay more than 5. - Well, then.

520
00:48:39,550 --> 00:48:40,840
八个就八个吧
Eight it is.

521
00:48:41,130 --> 00:48:42,390
我们能不能晚点再讨论这个
Perhaps we could discuss this later.

522
00:48:42,470 --> 00:48:44,260
我现在快撑不住你的左舷了
As I am having trouble here hoisting your port

523
00:48:44,340 --> 00:48:47,470
- 这根本不是左舷 是我的船尾 - 你确定吗
- You are far from port, That is my stern. - Are you sure?

524
00:48:47,560 --> 00:48:50,430
- 确定 - 好么 看啊
- Positive. - Well, look at this.

525
00:48:51,230 --> 00:48:53,940
如果我杀了那个懦夫 女巫会吊死
If I kill the coward. The witch hangs.

526
00:48:54,020 --> 00:48:56,900
- 一箭双雕 - 拜托不要放开我
- Two for the price of one. - Please don't let go of me.

527
00:48:56,980 --> 00:48:58,780
他杀掉我之后可能就很难保证这一点了
It might be difficult once he kills me.

528
00:49:04,360 --> 00:49:07,660
先生们 这两位囚犯将带领我们
Gentlemen, these two prisoners will lead us,

529
00:49:07,740 --> 00:49:09,160
去找三叉戟
to the trident.

530
00:49:11,160 --> 00:49:15,210
船长 你真觉得我们能找得到三叉戟吗
Captain. Do you really think we can find the trident?

531
00:49:15,290 --> 00:49:16,630
吉布斯船长 你这是自寻烦恼
Master Gibbs, you're worrywart.

532
00:49:16,710 --> 00:49:19,210
又没有什么好担心的
There is nothing to be concerned about.

533
00:49:21,970 --> 00:49:25,970
- 能出什么岔子呢 - 这就是你的计划吗
- What could possibly go wrong, right? - So this was your plan?

534
00:49:26,050 --> 00:49:27,550
被海盗们折磨杀害
To be tortured and killed by pirates?

535
00:49:27,640 --> 00:49:28,850
你说你需要一艘船的
You said you needed a ship.

536
00:49:28,930 --> 00:49:31,350
- 你管这叫船 - 切断缆索
- You call this a ship? - Cut the string!

537
00:49:39,980 --> 00:49:41,940
准备出发
Prepare to drown.

538
00:49:58,330 --> 00:50:00,550
我亲爱的船员们 终于
My dear beloved crew. Finally...

539
00:50:00,630 --> 00:50:01,510
今天
Today is...

540
00:50:12,810 --> 00:50:13,890
出问题了
Something's gone wrong.

541
00:50:33,410 --> 00:50:34,950
她浮起来了
She floats!

542
00:50:38,830 --> 00:50:40,840
正前方发现一只船
Ship dead ahead.

543
00:50:48,300 --> 00:50:49,300
长官
Sir.

544
00:50:50,930 --> 00:50:54,640
我们绝不会质疑您的决断
We would never question your reason as a captain.

545
00:50:54,720 --> 00:50:55,890
但是
But, however...

546
00:50:56,730 --> 00:50:59,400
您选择朝这个令人费解的方向
Is there a reason as captain, you've chosen...

547
00:50:59,480 --> 00:51:01,310
航行有什么原因吗
To sail in this unreasonable direction?

548
00:51:02,230 --> 00:51:04,320
告诉所有人准备迎战
Tell the men to prepare to be boarded.

549
00:51:04,400 --> 00:51:05,450
坚守阵地
To stand their ground.

550
00:51:05,530 --> 00:51:07,200
不要面带惧色
And show no fear.

551
00:51:12,870 --> 00:51:16,450
船长 有一艘船向我们这边驶来了
Capitan! A ship sails towards us.

552
00:51:42,610 --> 00:51:46,190
萨拉查船长 我听说你在寻找杰克·斯派洛
Captain Salazar. I hear you've been looking for Jack Sparrow.

553
00:52:09,840 --> 00:52:11,590
原地别动
Hold point!

554
00:52:14,470 --> 00:52:16,060
等候指令
And await orders.

555
00:52:36,910 --> 00:52:40,630
我是巴博萨船长 我今日来此
My name is Captain Barbarossa. And I stand before you,

556
00:52:40,710 --> 00:52:44,040
- 表达善意 - 我不需要什么善意
- with cordial intent. - I don't need any cordial intent.

557
00:52:44,250 --> 00:52:48,210
你听到没 这个海盗想要释放善意
Do you hear that? This pirate wishes to be cordial.

558
00:52:48,340 --> 00:52:52,050
我让你见识见识我的善意是什么
So let me show you what my cordiality is.

559
00:52:52,130 --> 00:52:54,340
我每敲一次剑
Every time I tap my sword.

560
00:52:54,840 --> 00:52:58,140
你的一名船员就会被杀掉 所以我建议你闲言少叙
One of your men will die, So I suggest you speak quickly.

561
00:53:02,270 --> 00:53:04,600
船长你可能得说快点
Might want to go a bit faster Captain.

562
00:53:08,270 --> 00:53:12,370
- 杰克·斯派洛在哪 - 杰克去寻找三叉戟了
- Where is Jack Sparrow? - Jack be sailing for the trident.

563
00:53:12,450 --> 00:53:15,870
- 不 海洋是属于亡灵的 - 三叉戟控制着海洋
- No. The sea belongs to the dead. - The Trident controls the seas.

564
00:53:15,990 --> 00:53:19,540
不 不 没有宝藏
No, no. There is no treasure.

565
00:53:19,620 --> 00:53:21,000
没有宝藏
There is no treasure.

566
00:53:21,080 --> 00:53:23,880
能够救得了他 他和你都会死
I can't save him. He'll die as will you.

567
00:53:23,960 --> 00:53:26,210
我是唯一一位能顾带你去找他的人
I be the only one that can lead you to him.

568
00:53:27,840 --> 00:53:31,050
我保证你能在明天日出前取走杰克的性命
I declare you should have Jack's life by sunrise tomorrow.

569
00:53:31,130 --> 00:53:34,470
否则到时你可以取走我的 我们达成共识了吗
Or you can take me on then. Do we have an accord?

570
00:53:41,390 --> 00:53:44,940
带我去找他 你就能活下来讲述这一切
Tail me to him. And you will live to tell the tale.

571
00:53:45,350 --> 00:53:47,190
我向你保证
You have my word.

572
00:53:47,360 --> 00:53:50,690
我代表我的船员谢谢你
I thank you on behalf of my crew.

573
00:53:55,030 --> 00:53:59,700
好了 你可以带走剩下的 活人入伙了
Okay. You can take what's left them. The living come aboard.

574
00:54:08,040 --> 00:54:10,220
卡丽娜 我们没多少时间了
Carina, we haven't got much time,

575
00:54:10,300 --> 00:54:11,800
亡灵们正朝我们驶来
the dead are sailing straight for us.

576
00:54:11,880 --> 00:54:14,090
- 是这样吗 - 是的 我和他们交谈过
- Is that so? - Yes, I've spoken to them.

577
00:54:14,170 --> 00:54:15,140
你和他们交谈过
You spoken to them?

578
00:54:15,220 --> 00:54:17,430
你是不是还和北海巨妖还有美人鱼说过话
Have you spoken to the Krakens and the mermaids as well?

579
00:54:17,720 --> 00:54:18,970
北海巨妖不说话 是个人就知道
Krakens don't speak, everyone knows that.

580
00:54:19,050 --> 00:54:21,770
当然 我就不该救你
Of course, I never should have saved you.

581
00:54:22,350 --> 00:54:25,060
昨晚出现了血月 正如你描述的那样
Last night there was a blood moon, just as you described.

582
00:54:25,140 --> 00:54:26,310
告诉我这揭示了什么
Tell me what to reveal.

583
00:54:26,390 --> 00:54:27,810
我为什么要相信你
And why should I trust you?

584
00:54:27,980 --> 00:54:29,940
你都让我托着你的走廊了 记得吗
You trusted me to hold your porch, remember?

585
00:54:30,070 --> 00:54:30,900
那是我的船尾
It was my stern.

586
00:54:30,980 --> 00:54:32,860
显然你还需要多在海上磨练磨练
Clearly you need to spend more time at sea.

587
00:54:32,940 --> 00:54:35,120
告诉我你发现了什么我保证会帮你
Tell me what you found and I promise to help you.

588
00:54:35,200 --> 00:54:35,990
我不需要帮助
I don't need any help.

589
00:54:36,070 --> 00:54:37,820
卡丽娜 那你为什么还要来找我
Then why did come to me Carina?

590
00:54:38,240 --> 00:54:39,910
为什么我们被绑在一起在海上
Why are we tied together in the middle of the sea...

591
00:54:39,990 --> 00:54:41,370
追寻同一份宝藏
Chasing the same treasure?

592
00:54:44,370 --> 00:54:46,080
月亮揭示了一条线索
The moon revealed a clue...

593
00:54:46,370 --> 00:54:48,460
要释放大海的力量
To release the power of the sea.

594
00:54:49,040 --> 00:54:52,130
- 必须分裂 - 分裂
- One must divide. - Divide?

595
00:54:52,300 --> 00:54:56,010
- 那是什么意思 - 我还不确定
- What does it mean? - I'm not sure yet.

596
00:54:57,930 --> 00:54:59,390
那么我们就去找答案
Then we'll find out.

597
00:55:01,300 --> 00:55:04,350
- 这个地图集里没有地图 - 把我的日记给我
- There is no map in this map. - Give me my diary.

598
00:55:06,100 --> 00:55:07,900
把无人能阅的地图给我
Give me the map no man can read.

599
00:55:07,980 --> 00:55:08,730
如果你能看得着
If you could read it.

600
00:55:08,810 --> 00:55:10,320
那就不会被叫做无人能阅的地图了
Then it wouldn't be call the map that no man can read.

601
00:55:10,400 --> 00:55:12,360
我拜托你 别和她争
I beg you please, don't argue with her.

602
00:55:12,820 --> 00:55:14,940
这艘船上大部分的人都不识字
Most of the men on this ship can't read.

603
00:55:15,690 --> 00:55:17,410
使得大部分的地图
Which makes all maps.

604
00:55:17,490 --> 00:55:19,450
对他们来说都是无法阅读的地图
Maps that no man can read.

605
00:55:19,530 --> 00:55:22,240
如果你读不了 那么你也就不需要它和我了
Well if you can't read it, then you've no use for it, or me.

606
00:55:23,450 --> 00:55:26,500
我重新说一遍 把地图给我看
Let me start again. Show me the map.

607
00:55:27,290 --> 00:55:29,460
我不能 它根本不存在
I can't. It does not even exist.

608
00:55:30,040 --> 00:55:32,710
- 她是个女巫 - 我是个星象家
- She's a witch! - I'm an astronomer.

609
00:55:33,920 --> 00:55:37,180
- 她养驴子 - 什么 不是
- She breeds donkeys. - What? No.

610
00:55:37,260 --> 00:55:40,890
- 星象家解读天象 - 是啊 在驴子上
- An astronomer contemplates the sky. - Yay, on a donkey.

611
00:55:40,970 --> 00:55:44,640
- 不 没有驴子的事 - 那么你是怎么养它们的
- No, there's no donkey! - Well then how do you breed then?

612
00:55:45,010 --> 00:55:49,140
让我简化一下这个交易 把地图给我
Allows me to simplify this equation. Give me the map.

613
00:55:50,850 --> 00:55:56,360
不然我就杀了他 杀了他
Or I'll kill... him, or kill him.

614
00:55:58,700 --> 00:56:01,490
来呀 你在虚张声势
Go on then. You're bluffing.

615
00:56:02,780 --> 00:56:04,370
你脸红了
And you're blushing.

616
00:56:06,160 --> 00:56:07,410
把他扔下海去
Throw him over.

617
00:56:11,920 --> 00:56:13,960
我们管这叫做拖龙骨
We call this keel hauling.

618
00:56:14,790 --> 00:56:17,170
小亨利会被扔下船去
Young Henry will be tossed over.

619
00:56:18,630 --> 00:56:21,130
被拖在船底
And he will be dragged under the ship.

620
00:56:21,340 --> 00:56:22,390
好吧
Alright.

621
00:56:22,890 --> 00:56:25,310
- 你还在等什么 - 他好像没有在虚张声势
- What're you waiting for? - He doesn't appear to be bluff there.

622
00:56:26,560 --> 00:56:29,180
不 我不虚张声势 他想说什么来着
No. Not bluffing me. He's trying to say something.

623
00:56:29,430 --> 00:56:32,060
不 不 我们船上没有食物了 抱歉
No, no, we don't have any food on board. Sorry.

624
00:56:33,190 --> 00:56:34,990
如果他走运的话 他会在
If he's lucky, he'll drown,

625
00:56:35,070 --> 00:56:37,530
船底的藤壶把他切成肋排之前淹死
before the barnacles shred him to ribbon.

626
00:56:37,690 --> 00:56:39,910
- 藤壶 - 像是上千把刀子
- Barnacles. - Like a thousands knives,

627
00:56:39,990 --> 00:56:42,950
划过你的脊背 当然 血腥味儿会招来鲨鱼
across your back. And of course, the blood attracts sharks.

628
00:56:43,030 --> 00:56:43,620
鲨鱼
Sharks?

629
00:56:43,700 --> 00:56:46,200
- 船首有鲨鱼 - 在哪
- Shark of the bow! - Where?

630
00:56:46,330 --> 00:56:49,540
我会说会不会游泳恐怕不是他最担心的问题了
I would say that swimming is no longer his primary concern.

631
00:56:50,040 --> 00:56:51,210
地图在那
The map is there.

632
00:56:51,750 --> 00:56:53,800
- 在哪 - 在你的手指尖上？
- Where? - On the tip of your finger?

633
00:56:53,880 --> 00:56:56,210
不 在天上
No. In the heavens.

634
00:56:56,500 --> 00:56:58,130
那本日记会把我引向
That dairy will lead me to a map,

635
00:56:58,210 --> 00:56:59,260
藏在群星之间的地图
hidden in the stars.

636
00:56:59,380 --> 00:57:01,880
拉他上来吧 我今晚就能找到
Let him up, I'll find it tonight.

637
00:57:02,010 --> 00:57:03,640
抱歉 拉不上来了
Sorry, can't bring him up.

638
00:57:03,720 --> 00:57:05,050
你自己去看
Look for yourself.

639
00:57:08,260 --> 00:57:10,930
就像我说的 脸红了
As I said... Blushing!

640
00:57:17,230 --> 00:57:18,690
无耻的海盗
Filthy pirate!

641
00:57:23,320 --> 00:57:26,750
大海被染成血色 一名被冲上岸的水手
The sea has turned to blood, a sailor washed ashore...

642
00:57:26,830 --> 00:57:30,370
在说三叉戟的事 他之前在寻找杰克·斯派洛
Talking about the Trident. He was looking for Jack Sparrow.

643
00:57:30,540 --> 00:57:33,330
那个将一位女巫从绞刑架上救下的海盗
The same pirate who saved a witch from the gallows.

644
00:57:33,670 --> 00:57:36,750
- 她才不是女巫 - 但你是
- She's no Witch. - But you are.

645
00:57:38,000 --> 00:57:42,050
- 而你要帮助我们 - 你害怕了吗 中尉
- And you're going to help us. - You afraid, Lieutenant?

646
00:57:42,720 --> 00:57:46,640
风雨欲来 你想要知道你能不能自保
As ships burning the night, you want to know if you can save your own.

647
00:57:47,680 --> 00:57:53,310
- 三叉戟是否存在 - 你要为我解读那面墙
- If the trident is real? - You are going to read that wall for me.

648
00:57:53,520 --> 00:57:56,150
否则你会被处死 大英帝国
Or you will die. The British Empire will have...

649
00:57:56,230 --> 00:58:00,400
将会得到三叉戟并称霸海洋 我想要知道那个海盗
The trident and rule the sea. I want to know where that pirate is going,

650
00:58:00,480 --> 00:58:01,820
带着那个女巫去哪了
with that witch.

651
00:58:02,990 --> 00:58:07,490
你的宿命就写在群星之中 我会为你设定航向
Your destiny is in these stars. I will set your course.

652
00:58:33,100 --> 00:58:34,680
不要意面墙
No Spaghetti walls.

653
00:58:35,850 --> 00:58:37,400
我干嘛费那个劲来找你
Why did I bother coming to you?

654
00:58:37,520 --> 00:58:39,810
亡灵在追杀我们你却在这里无所事事
The dead are haunting us down and you do nothing.

655
00:58:40,230 --> 00:58:43,490
- 无所事事 你管这叫无所事事 - 你喝得醉醺醺地呼呼大睡
- Nothing, You call this nothing? - You're drunk and you're sleeping.

656
00:58:43,570 --> 00:58:47,450
正是如此 我在一心二用
My point exactly, I am doing two things at once.

657
00:58:47,740 --> 00:58:50,200
你没法解救不可救之人
You can't save the unsavable mate.

658
00:58:51,660 --> 00:58:53,580
不管你喜欢与否 你都得帮助我
Like it or not Jack, you're going to help me.

659
00:58:53,660 --> 00:58:55,620
我会打破我父亲的诅咒的
I will break my father's curse.

660
00:58:58,170 --> 00:59:00,340
下次你再挥剑的时候 小伙子
Next time you raise a sword, boy.

661
00:59:01,290 --> 00:59:03,380
最好别死
Be the last to die.

662
00:59:19,600 --> 00:59:23,480
我建议你奉承她两句讨好她
Might I suggest you entice her with a bit of flattery.

663
00:59:24,690 --> 00:59:26,530
我来这是为了我的父亲 别无他求
I am here for my father, nothing more.

664
00:59:27,360 --> 00:59:30,240
我知道 早就烂熟于心了
I knew it, absolutely smitten with that.

665
00:59:30,910 --> 00:59:34,370
勾搭棕发美女有一点注意事项
Now, bit of discretion when goes into brunette.

666
00:59:34,450 --> 00:59:36,290
绝对不要追求她的姐妹
Never pursue her sister.

667
00:59:36,370 --> 00:59:39,790
如果你实在抵不住她姐妹的魅力
But if you can not avoid the charming sister.

668
00:59:40,290 --> 00:59:42,380
那就杀了哥哥 懂？
Kill the brother, savvy?

669
00:59:44,210 --> 00:59:45,920
不 我不懂
No, I do not savvy.

670
00:59:47,970 --> 00:59:52,220
谁伤了你 顺便说一句刚才的一点经验之谈
Who hurt you? By the way that little slim of knowledge.

671
00:59:52,300 --> 00:59:55,940
- 要25个先令 - 我才不会因为那个付你钱
- Has cost you five pieces. - I am not paying you for that.

672
00:59:56,020 --> 00:59:57,770
也别对女人说种句话
Never say that to a woman.

673
01:00:12,870 --> 01:00:15,950
你看不到不代表就不存在
Just because you can't see something does not mean it's not there.

674
01:00:17,370 --> 01:00:18,540
比如地图吗
Like the map?

675
01:00:20,710 --> 01:00:22,080
我们必须找到
We have to find it.

676
01:00:23,290 --> 01:00:25,090
这是弄清我和我父亲
It's the only link to who I am.

677
01:00:25,840 --> 01:00:27,510
身世的唯一线索
Who my father was.

678
01:00:28,880 --> 01:00:30,180
所以我们这辈子
So we both spent our lives,

679
01:00:30,260 --> 01:00:31,630
都花在了找寻我们的父亲上
searching for our fathers.

680
01:00:33,140 --> 01:00:35,140
也许你我要比你想象的更为相似
Perhaps you and I are closer than you think.

681
01:00:52,030 --> 01:00:54,490
太阳升起来了 所以是时候了
The sun is up. And so is up time.

682
01:00:57,370 --> 01:00:59,830
我无意辩驳 但是我们协议中的准确
I'm not to disagree, but the precision of our accord,

683
01:00:59,950 --> 01:01:01,170
时间是太阳升起后
Ends at sunrise.

684
01:01:01,250 --> 01:01:04,380
太阳才刚露头 离完全升起还早
This be will light, far from a fully rising sun.

685
01:01:04,460 --> 01:01:08,010
- 我知道您是位信守诺言之人 - 诺言 你根本不了解我
- And I know you to be a man of honor. - Honor, you know nothing of me.

686
01:01:08,090 --> 01:01:10,510
我知道被杰克·斯派洛打败是什么滋味
I know what it likes to be bested by Jack Sparrow.

687
01:01:10,590 --> 01:01:13,930
- 他是我们共同的敌人 - 你并不知道我是谁
- He's an enemy to us both. - You don't know who I am.

688
01:01:15,550 --> 01:01:20,180
我听说过一位强大的西班牙船长的故事 海上斗牛士
I've heard stories of a mighty Spanish captain. El Matador Del Mar.

689
01:01:20,350 --> 01:01:24,360
一位在海上纵横捭阖 追杀了成百上千的人
A man who skirts the sea. Hunted and killed thousands of men.

690
01:01:24,440 --> 01:01:25,730
不 不 不 不是人
No, no, no. Men, no, no.

691
01:01:25,810 --> 01:01:26,820
不
No.

692
01:01:27,480 --> 01:01:29,230
是海盗
Pirates! Eh?

693
01:01:31,570 --> 01:01:32,860
海盗
Pirates.

694
01:01:38,280 --> 01:01:41,580
海盗世世代代为祸海洋
Pirates had infected the seas for generations.

695
01:01:41,660 --> 01:01:44,920
夺去了我父亲和祖父的性命
Taken the life of my father and his father before.

696
01:01:45,210 --> 01:01:48,590
因此我发誓要一劳永逸地除掉这个祸患
So I vowed to end this plague once and for all.

697
01:01:48,590 --> 01:01:48,670


698
